n.org/datasets/1c7a301c8e6843f2b4fe63fdb3a9fe39|accessdate=August 5, 2019|title=U.S. Potential Natural Vegetation, Original Kuchler Types, v2.0 (Spatially Adjusted to Correct Geometric Distortions)}}</ref>\n\n==Notable people==\n{{Category see also|People from Barnegat Light, New Jersey}}\nPeople who were born in, residents of, or otherwise closely associated with Barnegat Light include:\n* [[Matt Cook (actor)|Matt Cook]] (born 1984), actor known mostly for his roles as Mo McCracken on the [[Turner Broadcasting System|TBS]] sitcom ''[[Clipped (TV series)|Clipped]]'' and as Lowell in the [[CBS]] sitcom ''[[Man with a Plan (TV series)|Man with a Plan]]''.<ref>Staff. [https://thesandpaper.villagesoup.com/p/island-native-matt-cook-stars-in-sitcom-clipped-premiering-tuesday-on-tbs/1359354 \"Island Native Matt Cook Stars in Sitcom ''Clipped'' Premiering Tuesday on TBS \"], TheSandPaper.net, June 9, 2015. Accessed October 9, 2017. \"Matt Cook, Island boy and Southern Regional High School alumnus, formerly of Barnegat Light and Ship Bottom, has landed a starring role in the new half-hour, multi-camera, live-studio-audience show by Max Mutchnick and David Kohan, the creators of ''Will and Grace.''\"</ref>\n* [[Tom MacArthur]] (born 1960), represents [[New Jersey's 3rd congressional district]] in the [[United States House of Representatives]].<ref>Mulvihill, Geoff via [[Associated Press]]. [http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2014/may/5/3rd-district-race-attracts-2-candidates-from-north/ \"Correction: NJ Congress-3rd District story\"], ''[[The Washington Times]]'', May 5, 2014. Accessed April 27, 2015. \"MacArthur, who has put $2 million of his own money into the campaign, said he had been spending about half his time at his home in Barnegat Light, which is near but not in the 3rd District, and was planning to move to Ocean County permanently.\"</ref>\n* [[Matt McAndrew]] (born 1990), singer-songwriter best known for his appearance in [[The Voice (U.S. season 7)|Season 7]] of [[NBC]]'s reality TV singing competition ''[[The Voice (U.S. TV series)|The Voice]]'' where he finished as the runner-up as part of [[The Voice (U.S. TV series)#Season 7|team Adam]].<ref>Hyman, Vicki. [http://www.nj.com/entertainment/tv/index.ssf/2014/11/the_voice_2014_recap_knockout_rounds_part_3.html \"'The Voice' 2014 recap: Final knockouts move Barnegat Light's Matt McAndrew into top 20\"], NJ Advance Media for [[NJ.com]], November 3, 2014. Accessed April 27, 2015. \"Of our Jersey contestants, two have made to the live rounds \u2014 Barnegat Light's Matt McAndrew, who got short shrift in tonight's episode but sounded great in the snippet of 'Drops of Jupiter,' and Ricky Manning, the Jersey City busker.\"</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n* Karch, Mary. ''Under the Lighthouse \u2013 Memories of Barnegat City.'' 2004, Down The Shore Publishing\n* Lloyd, John Bailey. ''Eighteen Miles of History on Long Beach Island.'' 1994, Down The Shore Publishing and The SandPaper, Inc.\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n* [http://www.barnegatlight.org/ Barnegat Light website]\n* [https://discoverbarnegatlight.com The Barnegat Light Tourism Coalition website]\n* [https://discoverbarnegatlight.com/directory/listing/barnegat-lighthouse-state-park Barnegat Lighthouse Visitor Information]\n* [http://www.lbischools.org Long Beach Island School District]\n* {{NJReportCard|29|2760|0|Long Beach Island School District}}\n* [https://nces.ed.gov/ccd/schoolsearch/school_list.asp?Search=1&DistrictID=3408910 School Data for the Long Beach Island School District], [[National Center for Education Statistics]]\n* [http://www.srsd.net/ Southern Regional School District]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Succession box\n | title  = Beaches of New Jersey\n | years  = \n | with   =\n | before = [[Island Beach State Park]]\n | after  = [[Loveladies, New Jersey|Loveladies]]\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Ocean County, New Jersey}}\n\n[[Category:Barnegat Light, New Jersey| ]]\n[[Category:1904 establishments in New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Borough form of New Jersey government]]\n[[Category:Boroughs in Ocean County, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:Jersey Shore communities in Ocean County]]\n[[Category:Long Beach Island]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1904]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barnegat_Light,_New_Jersey"}
{"title_page": "Ingus Jakovi\u010ds", "text_new": "{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name = Ingus Jakovi\u010ds\n| image =\n| league = [[Lega Basket Serie A]]\n| position = [[Point guard]]\n| height_m = 1.85\n| weight_kg = 82\n| team = Pallacanestro Varese\n| number = 7\n| nationality = Latvian\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|4|18}}\n| birth_place = [[Madona]], Latvia\n| career_start = 2009\n| career_end = \n| years1 = 2009\u20132010 | team1 = [[BK Gulbenes Buki]]\n| years2 = 2010\u20132011 | team2 = BAA R\u012bga\n| years3 = 2011\u20132014 | team3 = [[BK Liep\u0101jas Lauvas]]\n| years4= 2014\u20132016 | team4 = [[BK VEF R\u012bga|VEF R\u012bga]]\n| years5= 2016 | team5 = [[BC Nizhny Novgorod|Nizhny Novgorod]]\n| years6= 2016\u20132019 | team6 = [[BK Ventspils|Ventspils]] \n| years7= 2019\u2013present | team7 = [[Pallacanestro Varese|Varese]]\n| highlights   =\n*[[Latvian Basketball League|LBL]] champion ([[Latvian Basketball League|2015]])\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalSport | Men's [[Basketball]]}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{LAT}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship]]}}\n{{MedalSilver| [[2013 FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship|2013 Estonia]] | [[Latvia national basketball team|National Team]]}}\n}}\n'''Ingus Jakovi\u010ds''' (born April 18, 1993) is a Latvian professional [[basketball]] [[Guard (basketball)|guard]] for [[Pallacanestro Varese]] of the [[Lega Basket Serie A]]. He is also a member of the [[Latvian national basketball team]].\n\n== Professional career ==\nJakovi\u010ds started playing basketball for [[BK Gulbenes Buki]] in Latvian Basketball League 2nd division. In 2010, he spent a season with BAA Riga, which was a youth team that played in LBL D2. Year later he moved to [[BK Liep\u0101jas Lauvas]] where he played until end of the 2013 when his contract was bought out by [[BK VEF R\u012bga|VEF R\u012bga]].\n\nOn January 3, 2014, he signed with [[BK VEF R\u012bga|VEF R\u012bga]] until the end of 2015\u201316 season.<ref name=\"prime-athlete\">{{cite web|url=http://prime-athlete.com/news/ingus-jakovics-signs-a-three-year-deal-with-vef-riga/|title=Ingus Jakovi\u010ds signs a three year deal with VEF Riga - PRIME Athlete Management - PRIME Athlete Management|publisher=prime-athlete.com|accessdate=2014-07-28}}</ref>\n\nOn August 5, 2019, he has signed with [[Pallacanestro Varese]] of the [[Lega Basket Serie A]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportando.basketball/en/ingus-jakovics-joins-pallacanestro-varese/|title=Ingus Jakovics joins Pallacanestro Varese|date=August 30, 2019|publisher=Sportando|language=En|access-date=August 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== International career ==\nIn July 2013, Jakovi\u010ds helped Latvian U20 team to reach [[2013 FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship|U20 European Championship]] finals. During this tournament he averaged 13.6 points, 3.5 assists and 2.5 rebounds.<ref name=\"fibaeurope\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fibaeurope.com/cid_KNce8jInH7Qj1EsyH5rjn2.playerID_92258.compID_UIfgjyQcGqk-fPlnl66Tj0.season_2013.roundID_9350.teamID_2134.html|title=Ingus Jakovics &#124; U20 European Championship Men 2013 &#124; FIBA Europe|publisher=fibaeurope.com|accessdate=2014-07-28}}</ref> On July 14, 2014, he made debut for senior Latvian National Team in win over Estonia.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://basketball.eurobasket.com/player/Ingus_Jakovics/Latvia/VEF_Riga/192369 Eurobasket.com Profile]\n*[http://basket.lv/viriesu_izlase/show-nt-player/?nt_season_id=null&nt_player_id=1879583 Latvian National Team profile]\n*[http://basket.lv/lbl1/show-player?player_id=1879583 basket.lv Profile]\n\n{{Pallacanestro Varese current roster}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jakovics, Ingus}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:BC Nizhny Novgorod players]]\n[[Category:BK Liep\u0101jas Lauvas players]]\n[[Category:BK VEF R\u012bga players]]\n[[Category:BK Ventspils players]]\n[[Category:Latvian men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Lega Basket Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Pallacanestro Varese players]]\n[[Category:People from Madona]]\n[[Category:Point guards]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name = Ingus Jakovi\u010ds\n| image =\n| league = [[Lega Basket Serie A]]\n| position = [[Point guard]]\n| height_m = 1.85\n| weight_kg = 82\n| team = Pallacanestro Varese\n| number = 7\n| nationality = Latvian\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|4|18}}\n| birth_place = [[Madona]], Latvia\n| career_start = 2009\n| career_end = \n| years1 = 2009\u20132010 | team1 = [[BK Gulbenes Buki]]\n| years2 = 2010\u20132011 | team2 = BAA R\u012bga\n| years3 = 2011\u20132014 | team3 = [[BK Liep\u0101jas Lauvas]]\n| years4= 2014\u20132016 | team4 = [[BK VEF R\u012bga|VEF R\u012bga]]\n| years5= 2016 | team5 = [[BC Nizhny Novgorod|Nizhny Novgorod]]\n| years6= 2016\u20132019 | team6 = [[BK Ventspils|Ventspils]] \n| years7= 2019\u2013present | team7 = [[Pallacanestro Varese|Varese]]\n| highlights   =\n*[[Latvian Basketball League|LBL]] champion ([[Latvian Basketball League|2015]])\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalSport | Men's [[Basketball]]}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{LAT}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship]]}}\n{{MedalSilver| [[2013 FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship|2013 Estonia]] | [[Latvia national basketball team|National Team]]}}\n}}\n'''Ingus Jakovi\u010ds''' (born April 18, 1993) is a Latvian professional [[basketball]] [[Guard (basketball)|guard]] for [[Pallacanestro Varese]] of the [[Lega Basket Serie A]]. He is also a member of the [[Latvian national basketball team]].\n\n== Professional career ==\nJakovi\u010ds started playing basketball for [[BK Gulbenes Buki]] in Latvian Basketball League 2nd division. In 2010, he spent a season with BAA Riga, which was a youth team that played in LBL D2. Year later he moved to [[BK Liep\u0101jas Lauvas]] where he played until end of the 2013 when his contract was bought out by [[BK VEF R\u012bga|VEF R\u012bga]].\n\nOn January 3, 2014, he signed with [[BK VEF R\u012bga|VEF R\u012bga]] until the end of 2015-16 season.<ref name=\"prime-athlete\">{{cite web|url=http://prime-athlete.com/news/ingus-jakovics-signs-a-three-year-deal-with-vef-riga/|title=Ingus Jakovi\u010ds signs a three year deal with VEF Riga - PRIME Athlete Management - PRIME Athlete Management|publisher=prime-athlete.com|accessdate=2014-07-28}}</ref>\n\nOn August 5, 2019, he has signed with [[Pallacanestro Varese]] of the [[Lega Basket Serie A]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportando.basketball/en/ingus-jakovics-joins-pallacanestro-varese/|title=Ingus Jakovics joins Pallacanestro Varese|date=August 30, 2019|publisher=Sportando|language=En|access-date=August 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== International career ==\nIn July 2013, Jakovi\u010ds helped Latvian U20 team to reach [[2013 FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship|U20 European Championship]] finals. During this tournament he averaged 13.6 points, 3.5 assists and 2.5 rebounds.<ref name=\"fibaeurope\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fibaeurope.com/cid_KNce8jInH7Qj1EsyH5rjn2.playerID_92258.compID_UIfgjyQcGqk-fPlnl66Tj0.season_2013.roundID_9350.teamID_2134.html|title=Ingus Jakovics &#124; U20 European Championship Men 2013 &#124; FIBA Europe|publisher=fibaeurope.com|accessdate=2014-07-28}}</ref> On July 14, 2014, he made debut for senior Latvian National Team in win over Estonia.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://basketball.eurobasket.com/player/Ingus_Jakovics/Latvia/VEF_Riga/192369 Eurobasket.com Profile]\n*[http://basket.lv/viriesu_izlase/show-nt-player/?nt_season_id=null&nt_player_id=1879583 Latvian National Team profile]\n*[http://basket.lv/lbl1/show-player?player_id=1879583 basket.lv Profile]\n\n{{Pallacanestro Varese current roster}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jakovics, Ingus}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:BC Nizhny Novgorod players]]\n[[Category:BK Liep\u0101jas Lauvas players]]\n[[Category:BK VEF R\u012bga players]]\n[[Category:BK Ventspils players]]\n[[Category:Latvian men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Lega Basket Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Pallacanestro Varese players]]\n[[Category:People from Madona]]\n[[Category:Point guards]]\n", "name_user": "I dream of horses", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eProfessional career:clean up,typo(s) fixed: 2015-16 \u2192 2015\u201316", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ingus_Jakovi%C4%8Ds"}
